<title>FRANCE: Dexia raises Eurotunnel provision.</title>
<headline>Dexia raises Eurotunnel provision.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dexia, the bank formed by the merger of Credit Local de France and Credit Communal de Belgique, said on Tuesday it raised the provisions set aside for Channel Tunnel operator Eurotunnel in 1996.</p>
<p>&quot;The two principal provisions were once again for property and Eurotunnel. The provision set aside for the latter has been raised to 45 percent by the addition of 60 million francs,&quot; Dexia chairman Pierre Richard told a news conference.</p>
<p>&quot;We're waiting like everybody to find out more about the impact of the fire and for the commercial results,&quot; he said.</p>
<p>Its provision for Eurotunnel totals 280 million francs, up from 226 million in the previous year.</p>
<p>The bank added 192 million francs to its provision for property risk.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom, +33 1 4221 5452</p>
